    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Division of the plant kingdom containing conifers, which are gymnospermous exogens (stem grows by deposit on its outside), comprising trees and shrubs bearing cones; most are evergreen, with leaves that are needlelike, scale-like, with a single vein or, less commonly, strap-shaped with multiple veins.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
